name: health4all_v3
description: Health4All is a customisable application for various healthcare delivery settings, free and open source. This version is created on 12May2020, with copy of the live version. We hope to organise version control better in this one. Requesting volunteers to support this version. Health4All is currently used by over 25 large Free Government Hospitals, an equal number of Free Health Centers run by Non-Profits and also by 3 Free TeleHealth Consultation Facilities. Health4All started off as a basic patient registration module in 2012. Today it has expanded into a feature packed Hospital Management Information System and is being used across several Free Healthcare Institutions and Healthcare Delivery Models. In each of these settings it helps to improve the quality of patient care including reducing turn-around times of the services provided.
